cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the use of nonorthogonal multiple access (NOMA) for 5G networks to improve network capacity and reduce latency, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture.
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes an optimization framework for user clustering, resource allocation, and power control, which involves information theory concepts such as channel capacity and signal-to-interference-plus-noise ratio (SINR).
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with the design and optimization of a system that involves multiple components, such as mobile edge computing (MEC), NOMA, and power control, which falls under the scope of systems and control.
4. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper discusses the allocation of computing resources at the cloudlet to different users, which involves distributed computing concepts.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions the improvement of quality of service (QoS) for 5G networks, which may involve multimedia applications such as video streaming or real-time communication.
